records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the charge of felony possess firearm.  Convicted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of two and one-half (2.5) years.  That is twelve (12) months initial confinement followed by eighteen (18) months extended supervision, consecutive to the sentence presently being served on 09 CF 304.
The defendant is found not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) maintain fulltime employment and/or schooling;
3) maintain absolute sobriety;
4) pay court costs;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) provide DNA sample.
The State moves for destruction of the firearm after any co-defendant's cases have been disposed of.  Court grants motion and authorizes destruction of the firearm.
Minutes.
